THE GAME
--------

  'Thumper' is a Workbench game inspired by the 'sokoban'-type
games; you have to move various shapes with coloured patterns up
to their corresponding 'receiving' shapes. To move a shape, you
have to click on empty space, or any empty receiving shape,
located next to it in order to 'thump' (or push) on that shape.
If there are more than one shape that are placed next to the
position you click on, both shape will move, unless another shape
or wall is in the way...

  The usual 'sokoban' rules apply here: do not 'trap' any shape in
an inside corner, or along a continuous wall if there are no
receiving shape for it nearby, etc. If you do trap one (or more)
shape, you can restart a game board anytime...

  Complete each of the 25 game levels in the least amount of
moves.

  Have fun!

